description: It appears both Russia and Ukraine have withdrawn forces from the Siversk area to deploy in other areas. Russia is pretending to take advantage of this by launching failed attacks towards Verkhnokamyanske (2).

WKT: We say “towards” because Russia still hasn’t captured all of Luhansk oblast and has to fight through Ukrainian forces to even reach Verkhnokamyanske.

description: In Zaporizhzhia
column4: I see evidence of very heavy Ukrainian shelling of Russian positions (18). Ukrainian shelling of these areas has been going on for some time
column5: and Ukraine’s successful counter battery fire is why they are able to move south from Orikhiv

WKT: As Ukrainian counter battery fire continues to excel and degrade Russia’s own artillery
name: Ukraine’s offensive capability will increase and we could see a more robust thrust south. Although I doubt we will see a large offensive.
taking Tokmak is a significant priority for Ukraine. Their closest forces (not counting special forces or recon) are 24km north of Tokmak at the moment.
